## 1. Creating the VPC Peering Connection

**1-a.** From the AWS Management Console, search for **VPC** in the services search bar.

![Step 1a - Search for VPC](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/000019.awsstudygroup.com/10a1d3b26cf719036027b3f441d68df47cd5feab.png)

**1-b.** In the left-hand navigation menu, under **Virtual private cloud**, click on **Peering connections**.

![Step 1b - Navigate to Peering Connections](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/networkproguide.com/33590db0c8fd5611330dc204ecab40778233177d.jpg)

**1-c.** Click the **Create peering connection** button in the top-right corner.

![Step 1c - Create Peering Connection Button](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/networkproguide.com/33590db0c8fd5611330dc204ecab40778233177d.jpg)

**1-d.** Fill in the peering connection details:
- **Peering connection name tag:** Enter a descriptive name (e.g., `vpc-a-to-b-peering`).
- **VPC (Requester):** Select your first VPC (e.g., VPC-A) from the dropdown.
- **Account:** Select **My account** (or specify another account if cross-account peering).
- **Region:** Select **This Region** (or another region for cross-region peering).
- **VPC ID (Accepter):** Select your second VPC (e.g., VPC-B) from the dropdown.

![Step 1d - Peering Connection Form](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/networkproguide.com/694e5e5656ed4fc9a83bbd5cd77a82804d302a0e.png)

**1-e.** Click **Create peering connection**. You will see a confirmation banner indicating the connection has been requested.

![Step 1e - Peering Connection Requested](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/miro.medium.com/f1ae1b948741dc600290eb40417db214a9e90ed0.png)

**1-f.** The newly created peering connection will appear in the list with a status of **Pending acceptance**.

![Step 1f - Pending Acceptance Status](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/graphenedb.com/0c31c855ddd76b3f06175d5c5284021ae567f02f.png)

