## 2. Accepting the VPC Peering Connection

**2-a.** Select the peering connection you just created by clicking its checkbox.

**2-b.** Click the **Actions** dropdown menu and select **Accept request**.

![Step 2b - Accept Request Action](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/networkproguide.com/1874e9762475e193b676e54515252ca29b680fa4.png)

**2-c.** In the confirmation dialog, click **Accept request** to confirm.

**2-d.** Once accepted, the peering connection status will change to **Active**. You will also see a green success banner at the top.

![Step 2d - Active Peering Connection](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/miro.medium.com/692caa9a37e0e9cf47d2668e2f37cfb7a3dd6ad0.png)

**2-e.** Click **Modify my route tables now** in the success banner to proceed with routing configuration (or navigate to Route Tables manually).

![Step 2e - Modify Route Tables Now](https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/networkproguide.com/ee79f7030c40c1a8a29bb8b5327c3105f78b46fc.png)

