## 6. Cross-Peering DNS (Optional)

If you want instances in one VPC to resolve DNS names of resources in the peered VPC, you can enable DNS resolution.

**6-a.** Go to the **VPC Dashboard** → **Peering connections**.

**6-b.** Select your active peering connection.

**6-c.** Click the **Actions** dropdown and select **Edit DNS settings**.

**6-d.** Enable **Allow DNS resolution from accepter VPC to private IP** and **Allow DNS resolution from requester VPC to private IP**.

**6-e.** Click **Save**.

> **Note:** DNS resolution across peering requires that both VPCs have DNS hostnames and DNS resolution enabled in their settings.

